Here are the MSTest patterns for each scenario:

### 1. Windows-only tests — `[TestCategory]` + conditional skip

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("WindowsOnly")]
public void Registry_ReadsExpectedValue()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows.");

    // ... registry test logic
}
```

Or use a filter at the CLI: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=WindowsOnly"`

### 2. Skip in CI (requires local GPU)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void Render_ProducesExpectedOutput()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU.");

    // ... GPU test logic
}
```

Then in CI: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

### 3. Retry flaky tests — `[Retry]` (MSTest v3.8+)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // retries up to 3 times on failure
public async Task GetWeather_ReturnsValidForecast()
{
    var result = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync("Seattle");
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

> **Note:** `[Retry]` was introduced in **MSTest 3.8**. For older versions, you'd need a custom retry loop or a helper method.

### 4. Cleanup even on failure — `[TestCleanup]` or `try/finally`

```csharp
private string? _tempFile;

[TestInitialize]
public void Setup()
{
    _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
}

[TestMethod]
public void ProcessFile_WritesExpectedOutput()
{
    File.WriteAllText(_tempFile!, "test data");
    var result = FileProcessor.Process(_tempFile!);
    Assert.AreEqual("expected", result);
}

[TestCleanup]
public void Cleanup()
{
    // Runs after EVERY test, even if it fails or throws
    if (_tempFile != null && File.Exists(_tempFile))
        File.Delete(_tempFile);
}
```

`[TestCleanup]` is the idiomatic MSTest approach — it **always runs**, even on failure. For one-off cases, a `try/finally` inside the test method works too.

---

**Summary of key attributes:**

| Scenario | Attribute/Pattern |
|---|---|
| Platform-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` + `[TestCategory]` |
| Skip in CI | Environment variable check + `[TestCategory]` filter |
| Flaky/retry | `[Retry(N)]` (MSTest ≥ 3.8) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` method |
